title: Payment Transactions and Basic Operations
summary: Demonstrates sending basic payment transactions between accounts and verifying balance changes, which is fundamental for any Algorand application involving value transfers.

title: Using the TestNet Dispenser API
summary: Demonstrates how to use the TestNet Dispenser API to fund accounts, register refunds, and check funding limits for development and testing purposes on Algorand TestNet.

title: Working with AlgoAmount - Unit Conversion and Formatting
summary: Demonstrates all aspects of working with Algorand amounts including unit conversion between ALGO and microALGO, formatting for display, fee calculations, and using the fluent API for convenient amount creation.

title: ABI Byte Array Conversion Utilities
summary: Demonstrates comprehensive utilities for converting ABI byte arrays to Uint8Array format, handling simple arrays, dynamic arrays, nested structures, tuples, and complex mixed-type data structures for Algorand smart contract interactions.

title: Account Management and Funding
summary: Demonstrates various account management operations including creating accounts from environment variables, account persistence, priority of environment configuration, and account rekeying for enhanced security.

title: Creating and Deploying a Smart Contract Application
summary: Demonstrates how to deploy a smart contract application to the Algorand blockchain with custom approval and clear state programs, including template variable replacement and verification of the deployed application.

title: Creating and Managing Algorand Standard Assets (ASA)
summary: Comprehensive guide to creating Algorand Standard Assets with full metadata, managing asset opt-ins and opt-outs (both single and bulk operations), and handling asset balances safely.

title: Custom Error Handling and Transformation
summary: Demonstrates how to transform raw Algorand blockchain errors into user-friendly, application-specific error messages using error transformation pipelines during both transaction simulation and submission.

title: Finding Applications Created by an Account
summary: Demonstrates how to query all applications created by a specific account using the Algorand Indexer with pagination support, useful for building application management dashboards and contract governance tools.

title: Querying Transactions and Accounts with Indexer
summary: Demonstrates how to use the Algorand Indexer to look up transactions by ID, retrieve account information, and search transactions with filters and pagination.

title: Setting Up Debug Event Handlers
summary: Demonstrates how to configure debug mode and set up asynchronous event handlers to monitor and log application events, essential for debugging and understanding application behavior.

title: Account Rekeying During Application Creation
summary: Shows how to securely transfer account signing authority to a new key while simultaneously creating an application, demonstrating advanced account security patterns and validating that the rekeyed account can sign subsequent transactions.

title: Atomic Transaction Groups with Smart Contracts
summary: Demonstrates how to compose atomic transaction groups that combine payments and smart contract calls using various methods including generated clients, ABI method calls, and nested method calls with transaction arguments.
